Fundamentals of Red Hat Enterprise Linux – Personal Notes

1. Vim Editor Basics

Saving and Quitting
:w      → Save (write)
:wq or ZZ      → Save and quit

Copy and Paste

yy      → Copy (yank) a line
p       → Paste below the cursor
5p      → Paste the copied line 5 times

Deleting Text

dd      → Delete a line
4dd     → Delete 4 lines
d$      → Delete from cursor to end of line
dw      → Delete a word

Editing

cw      → Change word
u       → Undo last action
2. Visual Mode in Vim
v          → Character visual mode
Shift + v  → Line visual mode
Ctrl + v   → Block visual mode

3. Useful Linux Commands

whoami → Displays the current logged-in user
command1 ; command2 → Executes both commands sequentially
command1 && command2 → Executes command2 only if command1 succeeds
echo $? → Shows return code of previous command

Return Codes:
0 → Command executed successfully
1 → Command failed

4. File and Text Commands
cat      → Display contents of a file
head     → Display first 10 lines of a file
tail     → Display last 10 lines of a file
history  → Show previously executed commands

5. Piping
command1 | command2

Output of command1 becomes input for command2
Example:
ls | grep file

6. Directory Commands
cd → Change directory
mkdir directory_name → Create a directory
mkdir -pv hello/hi/go → Create nested directories
ls -ld directory_name → Show directory details

7. System Monitoring
w → Shows users currently logged into the system

8. Running Applications in Background
firefox & → Runs program in background

9. Command Line Shortcuts
Esc + . → Recalls previous argument

10. User Management
usermod -g group_name username → Change user's primary group

11. Pattern Searching
grep pattern filename

grep stands for Global Regular Expression Print
Used to search for specific patterns in files

12. Adding a User
useradd username → Create a new user
passwd username → Set password for user

13. SSH Management
SSH (Secure Shell) is a secure protocol used to connect to another computer remotely.

Generate SSH key:
ssh-keygen

Copy SSH key to remote server:
ssh-copy-id user@remotehost

14. Linux Directory Structure
/      → Root directory
/home  → User home directories
/root  → Root user home
/bin   → Essential commands
/sbin  → System admin commands
/etc   → Configuration files
/var   → Logs and variable data
/tmp   → Temporary files
/usr   → Applications and utilities
/dev   → Device files

15. File Permissions
Permissions control access to files.

r → read
w → write
x → execute

Example:
ls -l

-rwxr-xr--
User  Group  Others

Change permissions:
chmod 755 file.sh

Make file executable:
chmod +x script.sh

16. Changing File Ownership
Change owner:
chown user file.txt

Change owner and group:
chown user:group file.txt

17. Package Management (RHEL)
Install package:
sudo dnf install package_name

Remove package:
sudo dnf remove package_name

Update packages:
sudo dnf update

Search package:
dnf search package_name

18. Process Management
View running processes:
ps -> process status
ps aux

Real-time monitoring:
top

Kill process:
kill PID

Force kill:
kill -9 PID

19. Networking Basics
Check network interfaces:
ip a

Check connectivity:
ping google.com

Check open ports:
ss -tuln

20. Learning Resources
man command → Shows manual page
Example:
man ls

vimtutor → Interactive vim tutorial
